  "text": "HTTP filter factory registration and instantiation in Envoy (v1.31.2) follows a multi-stage process:\n\n## 1. Filter Factory Definition and Registration\nHTTP filter factories are defined as subclasses of `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` (envoy/server/filter_config.h:273), which provides the pure virtual method `createFilterFactoryFromProto()`. Filter factories use the `Registry::RegisterFactory` pattern to register themselves statically. Each filter implementation defines a factory class that inherits from `NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory` and implements the factory method to return a `FilterFactoryCb` (a callback function defined in envoy/http/filter_factory.h:24).\n\n## 2. Filter Chain Configuration During Startup\nWhen `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` is constructed (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc:346), it processes all http_filters from the configuration. The constructor uses `FilterChainHelper` template class (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h:68) to iterate through filter configs. For each filter:\n\n- `FilterChainHelper::processFilters()` (line 87) iterates through all configured filters\n- `FilterChainHelper::processFilter()` (line 105) retrieves the registered factory via `Config::Utility::getAndCheckFactory<NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory>()` and calls `factory->createFilterFactoryFromProto()` (line 145 in filter_chain_helper.h)\n- The returned `FilterFactoryCb` callback is wrapped in a filter config provider and stored in `filter_factories_` list\n\n## 3. Filter Chain Creation Per Connection\nWhen a new HTTP stream arrives at the connection manager, `HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()` (source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc:780) is called:\n\n- It calls `Http::FilterChainUtility::createFilterChainForFactories()` (source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.cc:17) with the pre-built `filter_factories_` list\n- This utility iterates through each filter's config provider and calls `manager.applyFilterFactoryCb()` on the `FilterChainManager`\n\n## 4. Per-Request Filter Instantiation\nThe `FilterChainManager` interface (envoy/http/filter_factory.h:70) is implemented by `FilterManager` (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:638):\n\n- `FilterManager::applyFilterFactoryCb()` (source/common/http/filter_manager.cc:551) creates a temporary `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl` object\n- It invokes the filter factory callback: `factory(callbacks)` - this is where the actual filter instance is created\n- The callback typically calls `callbacks.addStreamDecoderFilter()` to instantiate the filter\n- In `FilterChainFactoryCallbacksImpl::addStreamDecoderFilter()` (source/common/http/filter_manager.h:918-922), the filter is wrapped in an `ActiveStreamDecoderFilter` and added to the decoder_filters_ list for this stream\n\nThis design separates factory registration (static, at startup) from filter instantiation (dynamic, per-request), allowing factory methods to be simple pure virtual functions that return configured callbacks, which are then invoked to create actual filter instances when needed."
}

